post_text: So excited to serve Golf School District 67 as the new Superintendent! #strongerandbettertogether
text: So excited to serve Golf School District 67 as the new Superintendent! #strongerandbettertogether

post_text:
Dear Golf 67 Community,

I hope everyone is enjoying the summer!

My name is Dr. Susan Coleman, and I am honored and excited to serve as your new superintendent. Golf School District 67 is an extraordinary place for all students to learn and grow. In my short time here, I can see that the tradition of excellence is due to the wonderful people of our community and the hard work of our students and staff. I have dedicated my life to the teaching and learning of all students. I have served as a bilingual special education teacher, dean, principal, and assistant superintendent, among other roles. Personally, I am a wife and mother of two fabulous teenage boys (ages 17 and 19). I am confident that my experience, coupled with the outstanding staff and community of Golf 67, will ensure that we continue to enhance the learning experiences of all students.

post_text: Last Day as Superintendent of Golf School District 67 - hard to believe! Thank you to my amazing administrative team for partnering with me these past 7 years to make our district outstanding! Thank you to the best administrative assistant ever - Gina you were like my right arm! Thank you to Lisa and Elise for your special gifts that will be a keepsake forever! post_text: Talk to any person in Niles Township and they’ll have a story for how they or their family got here. Some are stories of recent immigration, others of being transported to these lands against their will. Still others are stories of fleeing oppression or relocating in search of greater prosperity. Our origin stories are as central to who we are as the cultures we are a part of and celebrate. For the past decade, Coming Together has explored some of the cultures present in our community. This year, we will explore something we all have in common: the stories of our journeys to Niles Township.

shared_text:
Village of Morton Grove Municipality
November 9, 2019 at 12:30 PM ·

Golf School District 67 hosted its 4th annual ELL Family Night. This is an opportunity for our community and families who speak a second language to enjoy a delicious dinner from various neighboring ethnic restaurants, learn about the District's ELL program and meet the District's Language Ambassadors.

In an effort to ensure all families feel welcome and informed, District 67 started a Language Ambassador Program. A Language Ambassador is a parent who is fluent in English and a second language including, but not limited to Arabic, Assyrian, Polish, Romanian, Spanish and Urdu. Raffle prizes and free books were a special bonus!

We're proud to have Mayor Dan DiMaria participate in this event.

Coming Together in Niles Township
November 15, 2018 at 1:01 PM ·

In its 10th season, Coming Together brings life to the cultural diversity of Niles Township by celebrating one culture every year. Book discussions, film screenings, crafted demonstrations, and other events highlight the culture’s contributions to society in the fields of science, literature, arts, education, and much more.

Dear Parents,
Please complete the Illinois 5 Essentials Survey about our schools. The 5 Essentials Survey is based on 5 factors that are key to school improvement. A report will be generated for our schools only if at least 20% of parents respond to the survey. We are currently at 6%.
Thank you for your participation!
